{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_44","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.javamoney.moneta:moneta-core:1.4.2`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4264-fails-java-run-org.javamoney.moneta-moneta-core-1.4.2-ab44452f\n\nThe original failing stage was the Java runtime test: `DefaultMonetaryAmountsSingletonSpiTest#getDefaultAmountTypeLoadsConfiguredAmountClass()` failed because it expected `org.javamoney.moneta.FastMoney` but got `org.javamoney.moneta.Money` (`human-intervention-logs/org.javamoney.moneta:moneta-core:1.4.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T15-33-57-736945Z.log`).\n\nThe logs suggest the agent likely found a valid fix, but the workflow failed afterward while persisting results / collecting metrics. In `human-intervention-logs/org.javamoney.moneta:moneta-core:1.4.2/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-35-44-237842Z.log`, the generated fix says `moneta-core` `1.4.2` reads `org.javamoney.moneta.Money.defaults.amountType` via `MonetaryConfig`, so the test should use `MonetaryConfig.setValue(...)` instead of `System.setProperty(...)`. That same log reports `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.javamoney.moneta:moneta-core:1.4.2 --stacktrace` as `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, and the later Gradle log is green (`human-intervention-logs/org.javamoney.moneta:moneta-core:1.4.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T15-35-44-247391Z.log`).\n\nHowever, `stats/org.javamoney.moneta/moneta-core/1.4.2/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and identical starting/ending commits, and the preserved branch no longer contains the generated `tests/src/.../1.4.2` project. Dynamic-access coverage is unavailable. There is also a follow-up native trace issue in `human-intervention-logs/org.javamoney.moneta:moneta-core:1.4.2/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-02T15-35-51-704757Z.log`: `runNativeTraceImage` throws `MissingResourceRegistrationError` for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter`, which may explain why coverage artifacts were not produced.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.javamoney.moneta:moneta-core:1.4.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T15-33-57-736945Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.javamoney.moneta:moneta-core:1.4.2/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-35-44-237842Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.javamoney.moneta:moneta-core:1.4.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T15-35-44-247391Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.javamoney.moneta:moneta-core:1.4.2/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-02T15-35-51-704757Z.log`\n- `stats/org.javamoney.moneta/moneta-core/1.4.2/execution-metrics.json`\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Recreate the `1.4.2` test change from the generation log in `DefaultMonetaryAmountsSingletonSpiTest` and restore the generated `tests/src/org.javamoney.moneta/moneta-core/1.4.2` project if needed.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.javamoney.moneta:moneta-core:1.4.2 --stacktrace` to confirm the Java/native tests still pass with the restored change.\n3. Investigate the `runNativeTraceImage` resource-registration failure for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter` and why the validated changes were not persisted to the preserved branch."}}
